# Per-owner GitHub auth for the fleet. Pair a repo OWNER with a Personal Access Token: the worker
# uses the matching token to clone/push/gh for that owner's repos. Owners with NO entry fall back to
# your default `gh` auth — so single-identity setups need nothing here.
#
# Copy to ~/.agentask/forge-tokens and `chmod 600` it (it holds secrets, and is NOT versioned).
# One "owner=token" per line; whitespace and "# comments" are ignored.
#
# No quotes around the token (a leading \" yields 401 Bad credentials; the parser strips them anyway).
# fAIctory=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# boldfield=ghp_yyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy   # optional — omit to use your logged-in gh account
